The paper deals with image super-resolution using deep neural networks, which is a topic closely related to computer vision (cs.CV). The proposed method involves learning a nonlinear mapping function, which is a common approach in machine learning (cs.LG) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI). The paper also mentions the use of real-world data, which could fall under multimedia (cs.MM) or information retrieval (cs.IR).
